onary' account of information, Frohmann challenges the central concept of information studies, thereby laying a foundation for a documentalist approach to emerging issues in the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aDocumentation. 0aInformation science. 0aSciencexSocial aspects. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066769108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442673779423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442673779.jpg  aPDA5EBK  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066769-1  UTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA7ENG  aPDA14ALL  aPDA1ALL